FT  07 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Improvement at John Haggas
John Haggas, worsted spinner, improved its pre-tax profit from Pounds 2.88m
to Pounds 2.93m and earnings per share from 9p to 9.1p in the year ended
June 30.
In the spinning division it was a year of consolidation with margins still
under pressure and activity improving but only slowly.
There was a similar picture in fabrics, but sales to Europe had increased
substantially, albeit at low margins.
The final dividend is 2p to hold the total at 3p.
